                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>ALEXANDER GORDON. In consequence of suspicion, I placed myself in a dark cellar adjoining the warehouse, and after about twenty minutes the prisoner came down. Then he went and tied the tobacco in question up, and let down his breeches and put the tobacco in; then he went on working until I came out of the place where I was concealed; and whon he was going away, I stopped him, and charged him with having stolen this tobacco, but he denied it. I told him it was no use to deny it, for I had been in such a place and had watched him, and then he took it out and acknowledged it.</p>
               <p>
